theodore roosevelt island is a   island and a national memorial located in the potomac river in washington , d.c.   the island was given to the american people by the theodore roosevelt association in memory of the 26th u.s. president , theodore roosevelt ; before that , the island had been known as my lord 's island , barbadoes island , mason 's island , analostan island , and anacostine island .

american islands : theodore roosevelt island , now a memorial , lies in this river & is accessible by footbridge from virginia

